Art Houghtaling about the COVID-19 school closure

span.span:
There is aBoard Meeting scheduled for Tuesday, April 21at 5:30 pm. The meeting will will be held in the high school gymnasium.
Board Meeting Agenda

Virtual Board Meetings will have a meeting moderator. Public participants are asked to mute their mics and leave them muted until called on to speak. In order to request to speak, public participants should us the "Raise Hand" tool. Remarks from the public will be limited to 2-3 minutes.

p.span: The calendar for Board Meetings will be updated in this space as they are scheduled.Board Meetings begin at 6:30 p.m.; executive sessions startat 5:30 p.m. In accordance with state recommendations, Board Meetings will be held via teleconferencing for the foreseeable future. PleasecontactFalls City School District Office for schedule verificationin the event there is a meeting cancellation.

span.span: Falls City School District provides well-rounded opportunities for students to become productive positive citizens and life-long learners
